title: ONNX export for `.int()` and `.long()` is messed up
body_html:
OS: MacOS, CentOS
Pytorch version: 0.4.0a0+c1d277c (idk if this is helpful)
How you installed PyTorch (conda, pip, source): source
Python version: 3.6.3
CUDA/cuDNN version: N/A
GPU models and configuration: N/A
GCC version (if compiling from source): clang 9

Minimal example: https://gist.github.com/jamesr66a/a8e4584ced2ef9563bda9bfc7d6fb67e

Tracing and exporting int() on Linux seemed to emit a Constant node with the literal value of the variable at tracing time. On my mac, it just fails saying there's no tracing state
